07:55:19Z","closed_at":"2020-11-14T00:25:10Z","author_association":"MEMBER","active_lock_reason":null,"body":"The repository now supports class weights when calculating `cls_conf` Cross Entropy (CE) Loss for unbalanced datasets. Class weights are computed as the inverse class frequency from the dataset labels here:\r\nhttps://github.com/ultralytics/yolov3/blob/7e6e1897ac5514ab0e2ae3e3357da8a9c744cfed/utils/utils.py#L52-L60\r\n\r\nThe weights can then be passed to the CE loss function here:\r\nhttps://github.com/ultralytics/yolov3/blob/7e6e1897ac5514ab0e2ae3e3357da8a9c744cfed/utils/utils.py#L261\r\n\r\nUnfortunately we are not able to improve performance in weighted training on `coco_100img.data` (using the same hyperparameters), despite the fact that the dataset, and coco itself is heavily unbalanced. We will keep this issue open to focus on class weighting of unbalanced datasets, as perhaps our results may improve in the future!\r\n![results](https://user-images.githubusercontent.com/26833433/56914278-fc886c00-6ab3-11e9-90cc-2f8533a9e413.png)\r\n\r\n","closed_by":{"login":"github-actions[bot]","id":41898282,"node_id":"MDM6Qm90NDE4OTgyODI=","avatar_url":"https://avatars.githubusercontent.com/in/15368?v=4","gravatar_id":"","url":"https://api.github.com/users/github-actions%5Bbot%5D","html_url":"https://github.com/apps/github-actions","followers_url":"https://api.github.com/users/github-actions%5Bbot%5D/followers","following_url":"https://api.github.com/users/github-actions%5Bbot%5D/following{/other_user}","gists_url":"https://api.github.com/users/github-actions%5Bbot%5D/gists{/gist_id}","starred_url":"https://api.github.com/users/github-actions%5Bbot%5D/starred{/owner}{/repo}","subscriptions_url":"https://api.github.com/users/github-actions%5Bbot%5D/subscriptions","organizations_url":"https://api.github.com/users/github-actions%5Bbot%5D/orgs","repos_url":"https://api.github.com/users/github-actions%5Bbot%5D/repos","events_url":"https://api.github.com/users/github-act